folder: West Street & Albany Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1)
#87-93 West Street, East Side, between Albany and Cedar Streets, (rear view), as seen from #74 Trinity Place. Building shown and bearing these numbers is the 28 story WEST Building.
August 20, 1929.

(2) The same, showing passage way bridge to Ferry at 101 West Street.
March 1931

(3) West Street and showing West Building.
1911

Photographs by,
P.L. Sperr,

folder: West Street & Carlisle Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
West Street, east side, north from but not including Carlisle, to but not including Liberty Streets. Prominent building shown is the West Street Building, No. 87-93. July 28, 1923.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.

folder: Piers 10 and 11., Hudson River, Manhattan, NY
text:
North River, piers 10 and 11,
West Street, west side, from Carlisle (left) to Albany (right) Streets, showing piers 10 and 11 North River, with the Hudson River and the New Jersey Shore line in the background. At the extreme right is seen a portion of the West Street Building at the N.W. corner of Albany Street and at the extreme left, a portion of the New York Post Building at the
S.W. corner of Carlisle Street.

August 20, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.
title: North (Hudson) River - Piers 10 and 11.

folder: West Street & Albany Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1) West Street, east side, from Albany to Carlisle Streets. Also shown is Albany Street, south side, east from West, to and including Greenwich Streets. August 15, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.

(2) The same, at a later date, showing the area after practically all the houses which formerly stood there were razed. Albany Street is seen on the left. April 17, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

(3) The same, from a different angle. Note the 5-story house at the N.E. corner of Carlisle Street in process of being demolished. Also shown (background) is the Singer Building, at the N.W. corner of Broadway and Liberty Street. April 17, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: West Street & Carlisle Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1) West Street,east side,from Carlisle(right),to Albany(left), Streets,showing a clearance where #80-86 formerly stood. The view is eastward and shows the rear of P.S.#29,a four story structure occupying the remaining half of this block and facing on Washington Street. July 2nd,1937

(2) West Street,north east corner of Albany. The prominent buildings shown across the skyline are the Bank of Manhattan and the Irving Trust Company. July 2nd,1937

Photographs by, P.L.Sperr,
